[SN]TITLE[SN]
Castle Huntly prison absconder Mark Chung arrested in Glasgow

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man who absconded from Castle Huntly open prison near Dundee two weeks ago has been arrested in Glasgow.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Mark Chung, who officers had advised the public not to approach, was detained on Tuesday afternoon after a police operation in the north of the city.
He had been reported missing from Castle Huntly at 10:00 on 3 October.
The 41-year-old is being held in police custody and is expected to appear at Perth Sheriff Court on Wednesday.
